responsibilities:
1. Engineering Equipment Maintenance Management: Responsible for overseeing regional engineering equipment maintenance operations, monitoring and enhancing the quality and efficiency of maintenance work within the area to ensure timely delivery, quality standards and cost control are met;
2. Maintenance Process Standards: Establish and refine maintenance procedures and operational standards for engineering equipment, encompassing daily operations, repairs, servicing, inspection management and other aspects to safeguard business continuity;
3. Maintenance Supplier Management: Establish supplier maintenance management mechanisms, encompassing supplier tendering, assessment, incentives, allocation, and replacement;
4. Incident Response: Manage engineering equipment work orders during store operations, track progress, quality and cost. Demonstrate proficiency in specialist disciplines (plumbing, electrical, refrigeration, etc.), develop contingency plans, and lead relevant personnel to swiftly resolve unexpected equipment failures;
5. Energy Consumption Management: Oversee energy usage of engineering equipment across stores within the region, implement energy-saving measures, and achieve store-level energy reduction targets.

